courses.learning_outcomes:
To understand the concepts and basic principles of hydrologic cycle and the role of water in the earth and environmental systems;
To characterize and estimate the major components of hydrologic cycle;
To apply the knowledge and skills acquired to analyze the interactions of various hydrologic components and their influences on water availability and hazards;
To understand the general characteristics of water resources in Hong Kong, mainland China and the world

After taking this course, students will be able to:

* Gain knowledge of concepts, theories and scopes of public health practice;
* Articulate determinants of health and key epidemiology methodologies in public health studies;
* Understand theories of occupational and environmental health and apply roles in public health practice;
* Learn skills of identification of hazards and conduct health risk assessment to tackling important public health issues;
* Apply public health theories in important areas including air pollution, climate change and population health; food security, sustainability and population health; water pollution, land use and population health; etc. In addition, health promotion, healthcare management and policy implications will be discussed in these sessions.
